The paper deals with algorithms for computing graph cuts, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper focuses on two specific problems, balanced sparse cut and k-vertex connectivity, and provides subquadratic time algorithms for both. These problems are related to data structures, computational geometry, graph theory, and network analysis, which are all covered by different sub-categories in arXiv CS. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture).
